<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>RE:ench (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Adeline</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Hello Verondres.  First of all, I think you picked a good race.  Having that much INT is nice since sometimes we have to cast many spells in a fight.  CHA of 95 isn't bad either.  My character is a High Elf, base INT of 126 I believe (I have 2 +INT items), and base CHA of 100.  About our pets, they do ok, and if you manage to keep the creature stunned, then your pet will not take much damage.  I have learned not to let my pet tank completely for me, I go in and take a few hits myself and if the monster agroes on me I root it, but I'm not much for soloing and try to find a group as much as I can.  As for our spells, we're not wizards, so I don't blast very much when I'm in a group.  I just try to keep the monsters under control if we get more than 1.  This is coming from a lvl 12 enchantress, I don't know how we are past that.  But overall I am very happy with my character.  Enchanters are challanging and it takes some tought to play one right.  Don't make the mistake of playing your enchanter like a wizard, you'll make a lot of people unhappy.  We work behind the sceenes, making sure everything turns out right.  They will appreciate you a lot if you keep monsters stunned and mesmerized.  Tanks love you too once you can give them the speed buffs.  Happy hunting!</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
