<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>RE:ench (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Mo<br>
rphos</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">The beauty of the Enchanter is the variety of tactics available. Tactics being the operative word. We can group effectively with our buffs and debuffs and crowd control skills. I solo'd aviak guards in Lake Rathe in the low 20's and still solo Aviak Avocets at level 36. Tactic i use is Entrance, Tashani, Tepid Deeds, then Anarchy for 279 damage. When the avo attacks the pet gets in and i Color Shift to stun and back away. then <br>
cast Chase the moon to fear the avo, meanwhile my pet is beating away at the bird  while taking no damage as the bird runs away and i alternate Anarchy for 279 and Chaotic Feedback for 150 damages respectively until the bird dies. Still good experience. Works like a charm. If you find a ranger or druid with snare you can use  tactic on many things in the open spaces of the Karanas or oasis.<br>
Im probably the worst possible race choice being human so my int is a pitiful 120 however charisma is the primary stat for us it is the basis for all the mez and charm spells. I do get an experience bonus however and that has enabled me to level faster than i might as another race. When in a group never have a pet. It only gets you in trouble  by attacking something that you would prefer  to mez and the like. Better to Charm a creature and set it against its friends and change the odds dramatically. You need to be the quarterback in any group. Letting the group know what you are doing and to which creatures. keep the whole field in view. I'm forever running around the battle selecting tarets to mez and debuff and Making sure my healer is not being interupted. You cant be lazy and be an effective enchanter thats for sure.<br>
It is the most fun class i have played. You will need to educate the groups you are with <br>
on how to play with you but it will be worth it. <br>
The nicest compliment i've gotten is from a<br>
guy that said he didnt want to group with me.<br>
He said that someone told him that grouping with me made them seem like lvl 50's  Everything was too easy and it was no fun<br>
The nicest thing he could have said :)<br>
Have fun!!</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
